<TITLE> BCL cadres beat up journos at JU </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jahangirnagar University, May 16 (bdnews24.com) -- Pro-government Bangladesh Chhatra League cadres on Sunday beat up journalists at Jahangirnagar University. JU campus correspondents, in protest, brought out a silent procession and gave the administration 48 hour to bring those responsible to account.. BNP-backed Jatiyatabadi Shikkhak Forum and the Progressive Students' Alliance issued separate statements in protest. Witnesses said the clash began in front of the chairman's room at the economics department when Emon Rahman, the victim, went there to check his third-year exam results at around 11am. He got involved in a heated exchange with Samrat, another economics student and an activist of the ruling Awami League's student wing who then assaulted him. . Later, when other journalists went to the department chair to complain, Samrat stopped them and again beat Emon. Meanwhile, some 25 BCL cadres, led by Nahidur Rahman Sagar of Bhashani Hall, took position in front of the social sciences building. Samrat and some other cadres then beat up Emon when he and the other journalists came down to the ground floor. The president of the university journalists association, Rejaul Haque Kowsik, and vice president Sazzad Biplob were also beaten up. Later, when the journalists were returning after meeting the chairman, they were threatened in front of Amar Ekushey, a sculpture on campus. The journalists arranged a silent procession at 1pm following the incident. They submitted a memorandum, signed by 23 journalists, addressed to the vice-chancellor and the proctor, demanding permanent suspension of the assailants within 48 hours. bdnews24.
